From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sisyphus <noreply@example.com>
Date: Mon, 1 Jun 2026 16:40:00 +0900
Subject: [PATCH] board: ti: am64x: force usb-only boot policy after usb rom boot

When SPL was entered from BOOT_DEVICE_USB, the default U-Boot env still kept
the generic mmc-first boot policy:

  bootcmd=run envboot; run bootcmd_ti_mmc; bootflow scan -lb
  boot_targets=mmc1 mmc0 usb pxe dhcp

That means SD-inserted runs naturally prefer SD paths even if the early
bootloader chain came from USB. For USB-only autoboot rehearsal, make the
policy explicit by overriding boot, boot_targets, and bootcmd when the boot
device is USB.

This is a rehearsal-only patch and should be documented as such in the bringup
repo.
---
 board/ti/am64x/evm.c | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

diff --git a/board/ti/am64x/evm.c b/board/ti/am64x/evm.c
index 0000000000..1111111111 100644
--- a/board/ti/am64x/evm.c
+++ b/board/ti/am64x/evm.c
@@
 #ifdef CONFIG_BOARD_LATE_INIT
 int board_late_init(void)
 {
+	if (IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_USB_STORAGE) && spl_boot_device() == BOOT_DEVICE_USB) {
+		env_set("boot", "usb");
+		env_set("boot_targets", "usb");
+		env_set("bootcmd", "bootflow scan -lb");
+	}
+
 	if (IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_TI_I2C_BOARD_DETECT)) {
 		struct ti_am6_eeprom *ep = TI_AM6_EEPROM_DATA;
 
